|}Buras was split off from the [[Buras-Triumph, Louisiana|Buras-Triumph CDP]] prior to the [[2010 U.S. Census|2010 U.S. census]]. In the pre-Katrina period (before August 29, 2005) Buras had about 30-40 [[Cambodian American|Cambodian]] shrimpers, presenting the area's large [[Asian Americans|Asian American]] population. In the post-Hurricane period (after August 29, 2005) Brenda Kap, quoted in ''[[The New York Times]]'', stated most of them had returned.<ref>{{cite news|author=Longman, Jeré|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2006/11/03/sports/othersports/03parish.html|title=Mother Helps Her Son Find a Safe Harbor in Football|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|date=2006-11-03|accessdate=2016-12-03}}</ref> At the [[2020 United States census]], its Asian population was 344, making them the second-largest racial and ethnic group in the CDP; [[Non-Hispanic or Latino whites|non-Hispanic and Latino whites]] made up 471 persons total, and [[African Americans|Black and African Americans]] were the third largest group.<ref name="2020CensusP2" />

